{
  "//": "rio-worker seccomp profile (Localhost). See docs/src/security.md r[worker.seccomp.localhost-profile].",
  "//provenance": "Derived from Docker/moby default.json v27.5.1 (RuntimeDefault equivalent), flattened to OCI runtime spec format for the worker cap set (CAP_SYS_ADMIN + CAP_SYS_CHROOT). The Docker profile uses includes/excludes preprocessing which is Docker-specific; kubelet Localhost profiles are consumed by runc/crun which expect the OCI LinuxSeccomp format. Flattening: resolve the conditional blocks for the capabilities the worker actually has, drop the rest.",
  "//denied": "ptrace, bpf, setns, process_vm_readv, process_vm_writev — absent from ALL allow blocks, so defaultAction=ERRNO(EPERM) applies. Under RuntimeDefault these ARE allowed: ptrace/process_vm_* via the minKernel:4.8 block (always active on modern kernels), bpf/setns via the CAP_SYS_ADMIN block (worker has that cap). A sandbox escape inside the worker would have these tools; this profile takes them away.",
  "//why-each": {
    "ptrace": "debugger attach — lets an escapee inspect/modify other worker processes sharing the PID namespace",
    "bpf": "load eBPF programs — kernel-side code execution surface",
    "setns": "join another namespace — defeats namespace isolation (worker CREATES namespaces via unshare/clone, never JOINS existing ones)",
    "process_vm_readv": "cross-process memory read without ptrace — same attack class as ptrace",
    "process_vm_writev": "cross-process memory write without ptrace"
  },
  "//kept-from-cap-sys-admin": "mount/umount/umount2/unshare/clone/clone3/fsconfig/fsmount/fsopen/fspick/mount_setattr/move_mount/open_tree/pivot_root — worker needs these for overlayfs per-build isolation + Nix sandbox namespace setup. pivot_root is NOT in containerd's RuntimeDefault CAP_SYS_ADMIN block (upstream gap) but nix-daemon's build sandbox requires it; added here so the Localhost profile works where RuntimeDefault doesn't. fanotify_init/lookup_dcookie/perf_event_open/quotactl/quotactl_fd/setdomainname/sethostname/syslog kept for RuntimeDefault parity (low risk, removing them is a behavior change vs RuntimeDefault beyond the plan scope).",
  "defaultAction": "SCMP_ACT_ERRNO",
  "defaultErrnoRet": 1,
  "architectures": [
    "SCMP_ARCH_X86_64",
    "SCMP_ARCH_X86",
    "SCMP_ARCH_X32",
    "SCMP_ARCH_AARCH64",
    "SCMP_ARCH_ARM"
  ],
